article.headline: Oklahoma St beats No. 19 LSU for 3rd place

images.name: McGriff drains long 3 for OK State
images.caption: Cameron McGriff drains a long 3 to extend Oklahoma State's lead over LSU in the second half.

article.linkText: Oklahoma St beats No. 19 LSU for 3rd place
article.story: LAKE BUENA VISTA, Fla. -- Cameron McGriff had 28 points, Lindy Waters added 16, and Oklahoma State defeated No. 19 LSU 90-77 in the third-place game Sunday. Oklahoma State (4-2) beat Memphis 84-64 and lost to defending national champion Villanova 77-58 earlier in the invitational. The Cowboys were 6-6 against ranked teams last season. Skylar Mays scored 20 points for the Tigers (5-2), who were coming off a 79-76 overtime loss to No. 14 Florida State on Friday. McGriff hit a 3 and Waters made three free throws during a second-half opening 15-2 run that put Oklahoma State ahead 57-39 with 13 minutes to play. Michael Weathers layup extended the Cowboys lead to 68-48 midway through the second half. LSU missed 12 of its 13 shots during the Cowboys' surge. McGriff had 13 points as Oklahoma State grabbed a 42-37 halftime advantage. The Cowboys lead by 13 points 5 1/2 minutes into the game.

videos.headline: Waters drains big 3 early for OK State
videos.description: Lindy Waters III drains a big 3-pointer as Oklahoma State is out in front early vs. LSU.
